Analyze the layout structure of this resume markdown. Identify multi-column layouts at both the top level and within individual subsections.

A multi-column layout means content is arranged side-by-side rather than in a single vertical flow. Key indicators:
- Sections or items placed on the same horizontal line
- Tabular arrangements of skills, languages, or other items
- Sidebars divided by horizontal rules (---) or other visual separators
- Two or more distinct columns of text running in parallel

